    <div id = "about-site-container" class = "container">
      <h1>about the site</h1>
      <div>
        <p>The site is responsive, I used <strong>Bootstrap v4.6</strong>. For some parts I used native <strong>JavaScript</strong>, but I also used the <strong>jQuery</strong> library. Backend was written in <strong>Node.js</strong> using <strong>Express 4</strong>. The templating language is <strong>EJS</strong>. I used <strong>GitHub</strong> for version controlling. The site is deployed on <strong>Heroku</strong> (obviously). The <strong>MySQL</strong> server I use is <strong>ClearDB</strong> and for <strong>no-SQL</strong> database I use <strong>MongoDB</strong>.</p>
        <p>Each site in the 'things I can do' section represents a different skill. Neither of them was created by following a step-by-step tutorial. The next improvement will be a sign in / out feature using <strong>Passport.js</strong> to restrict the news editor for authenticated users only.</p>
        <p>Currently I am learning <strong>React</strong>, also plan to learn the basics of <strong>Angular</strong> and later on, <strong>Python</strong>.</p>
        <p>Github repository: <a href = "https://github.com/stregie/heroku-about-me">https://github.com/stregie/heroku-about-me</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id = "sites-list" class = "container">
      <h1>sites</h1>
        <div class = "sites-list-container col-xl-10 offset-xl-1">
          <div class = "row">
            <div class = "col-md-4">
              <a href = "/snake/"><img class = "img-fluid bordered-box" src = "/images/main/snake.jpg"></a>
            </div>
            <div class = "col">
              <a href = "/snake/"><h4>Snake</h4></a>
              <p>In-browser version of the classic snake game, created with native JavaScript. Highscores are stored in a MySQL database.</p>
              <p>The game can be played on desktop only.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class = "sites-list-container col-xl-10 offset-xl-1">
          <div class = "row">
